(1) Find the smallest positive period of the function;

(2) Find the intervals of monotonic increase of the function;

(3) If $x\in\left[0, \frac{\pi}{2}\right]$ and the minimum value of $f(x)$ is $-2$, find the value of $a$.

Given $f(x) = 2\sqrt{3}\sin x \cos x + 2\cos^2x - 1$,

