(2) In $\triangle ABC$, if $a$, $b$, and $c$ are the lengths of sides opposite the angles $A$, $B$, and $C$ respectively, with $a=1$, $b=\sqrt{3}$, and $f(A) = 2$, determine the angle $C$.

Given the following propositions:

(1) The graph of the function $y=3^{x} (x \in \mathbb{R})$ is symmetric to the graph of the function $y=\log_{3}x (x > 0)$ with respect to the line $y=x$;

(2) The smallest positive period of the function $y=|\sin x|$ is $2\pi$;

(3) The graph of the function $y=\tan (2x+\frac{\pi}{3})$ is centrally symmetric about the point $\left(-\frac{\pi}{6},0\right)$;

(4) The monotonic decreasing interval of the function $y=2\sin \left(\frac{\pi}{3}-\frac{1}{2}x\right), x \in [-2\pi, 2\pi]$ is $\left[-\frac{\pi}{3},\frac{5\pi}{3}\right]$.

The correct proposition numbers are $\boxed{(1)(3)(4)}$.

